%5B%7B%22title%22%3A%22Adding%20one%20line%20of%20code%20can%20now%20prevent%20OpenAI%20from%20accessing%20a%20website's%20data%20to%20train%20ChatGPT%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224711%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Photo%20illustration%20showing%20ChatGPT%20and%20OpenAI%20logos.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64d1ecbc7d2e90001945df46%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223533%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EJust%20one%20line%20of%20code%20can%20now%20prevent%20OpenAI%20from%20accessing%20a%20website's%20data%20to%20train%20ChatGPT.%3Cp%3EGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EOpenAI%20launched%20a%20new%20web%20crawler%20called%20GPTBot%20to%20browse%20the%20internet%20and%20collect%20information.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EHowever%2C%20adding%20one%20line%20of%20code%20to%20a%20website%20will%20block%20the%20crawler%20from%20accessing%20the%20site's%20data.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EBefore%20this%20post%2C%20OpenAI%20had%20not%20specified%20what%20data%20it%20used%20to%20train%20GPT-4.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EAdding%20just%20one%20line%20of%20code%20to%20a%20website%20will%20now%20block%20OpenAI%20from%20using%20the%20site's%20data%20to%20train%20its%20AI%20models.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EChatGPT%20creator%20OpenAI%20launched%20a%20new%20web%20crawler%20%E2%80%94%20called%20GPTBot%20%E2%80%94%20along%20with%20instructions%20for%20how%20to%20block%20it%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theverge.com%2F2023%2F8%2F7%2F23823046%2Fopenai-data-scrape-block-ai%5C%22%3Evarious%3C%2Fa%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fsea.mashable.com%2Fapps-and-software%2F25876%2Fopenai-launches-webcrawler-gptbot-and-instructions-on-how-to-block-it%5C%22%3Epublications%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.searchenginejournal.com%2Fopenai-launches-gptbot-how-to-restrict-access%2F493394%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eincluding%20the%20Search%20Engine%20Journal%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20reported%20Monday.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20web%20crawler%20is%20a%20bot%20that%20browses%20the%20internet%20to%20collect%20information.%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdevelopers.google.com%2Fsearch%2Fdocs%2Fcrawling-indexing%2Foverview-google-crawlers%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ESearch%20engines%20like%20Google%20use%20web%20crawlers%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0to%20collect%20information%20for%20their%20search%20results%2C%20while%20AI%20companies%20use%20these%20crawlers%20to%20collect%20data%20to%20train%20their%20models.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOpenAI%20launched%20the%20bot%20and%20instructions%20to%20block%20the%20crawler%20by%20adding%20a%20line%20of%20code%20to%20a%20website's%20%26quot%3Brobots.txt%26quot%3B%20file%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fplatform.openai.com%2Fdocs%2Fgptbot%5C%22%3Eaccording%20to%20a%20notice%20on%20the%20company's%20website%3C%2Fa%3E.%20It%20is%20not%20immediately%20clear%20when%20the%20notice%20was%20posted.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWebsite%20owners%20can%20also%20selectively%20allow%20GPTBot%20access%20to%20specific%20pages%20on%20their%20sites%2C%20per%20OpenAI's%20post.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20company%20added%20in%20the%20post%20that%20GPTBot%20filters%20out%20those%20sources%20that%20require%20paywall%20access%2C%20are%20known%20to%20gather%20personally%20identifiable%20information%20or%20have%20text%20that%20violates%20company%20policies.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20one%20professor%20thinks%20OpenAI's%20disclosure%20is%20less%20about%20individual%20privacy%20and%20more%20about%20appeasing%20large%20rights%20holders%20%E2%80%94%20such%20as%20media%20outlets%20and%20stock%20photo%20libraries.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat's%20as%20most%20of%20the%20sensitive%20information%20about%20individuals%20largely%20exists%20on%20websites%20where%20they%20cannot%20modify%20the%20code%2C%20Michael%20Veale%2C%20an%20associate%20professor%20of%20digital%20regulation%20at%20University%20College%20London%2C%20told%20Insider%20on%20Tuesday.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBefore%20this%20post%2C%20OpenAI%20had%20not%20specified%20what%20data%20it%20used%20to%20train%20GPT-4%20%E2%80%94%20the%20AI%20model%20behind%20ChatGPT%20%E2%80%94%20and%20whether%20it%20included%20social%20media%20posts%20and%20copyrighted%20works%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theverge.com%2F2023%2F3%2F15%2F23640180%2Fopenai-gpt-4-launch-closed-research-ilya-sutskever-interview%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethe%20Verge%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.technologyreview.com%2F2023%2F04%2F19%2F1071789%2Fopenais-hunger-for-data-is-coming-back-to-bite-it%2F%5C%22%3EMIT%20Technology%20Review%3C%2Fa%3E%20reported.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOpenAI's%20internet%20scraping%20has%20landed%20it%20in%20hot%20water%20with%20authors%20and%20artists.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFive%20authors%C2%A0filed%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fopenai-copyright-lawsuit-authors-chatgpt-trained-on-books-2023-7%5C%22%3Etwo%3C%2Fa%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhy-comedian-sarah-silverman-is-suing-the-company-behind-chatgpt-2023-7%5C%22%3Eseparate%3C%2Fa%3E%20lawsuits%20against%20OpenAI%2C%20claiming%20the%20company%20violated%20copyright%20law%20by%20using%20their%20books%20to%20train%20its%20AI%20models.%20Separately%2C%20over%208%2C000%20writers%20%E2%80%94%20including%20James%20Patterson%20and%20Margaret%20Atwood%20%E2%80%94%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-companies-thousands-authors-demand-compensation-for-using-works-2023-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esigned%20an%20open%20letter%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0demanding%20that%20OpenAI%20and%20other%20AI%20companies%20compensate%20them%20for%20the%20unauthorized%20use%20of%20their%20works.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOpenAI%20did%20not%20immediately%20respond%20to%20a%20request%20for%20comment%20from%20Insider%2C%20sent%20outs