3Cp%3EThe%20analysis%20found%20that%20the%20fully%20remote%20companies%20in%20the%20study%20had%20head-count%20growth%20rates%20over%20double%20those%20of%20fully%20in-person%20companies.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20findings%20were%20released%20against%20a%20backdrop%20of%20many%20major%20companies%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcompanies-making-workers-employees-return-to-office-rto-wfh-hybrid-2023-1%5C%22%3Erequiring%20employees%20to%20return%20to%20the%20office%3C%2Fa%3E%20full%20time.%20JPMorgan%20asked%20half%20its%20employees%20to%20return%20to%20the%20office%20five%20days%20a%20week.%20Goldman%20Sachs%20asked%20employees%20to%20return%20to%20the%20office%20five%20days%20a%20week%20as%20well%2C%20while%20companies%20such%20as%20Google%20and%20Apple%20have%20asked%20workers%20to%20come%20in%20at%20least%20three%20days%20a%20week.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22raw%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%3Ciframe%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdatawrapper.dwcdn.net%2FQYvjo%2F2%2F%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22Growth%20in%20employment%20by%20days%20required%20in%20the%20office%5C%22%20data-external%3D%5C%221%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22318%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.shrm.org%2Fresourcesandtools%2Fhr-topics%2Femployee-relations%2Fpages%2Fwhy-ceos-want-employees-return-to-office.aspx%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EIn%20a%20survey%20by%20the%20Society%20for%20Human%20Resource%20Management%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20many%20company%20leaders%20said%20they%20felt%20workers%20were%20more%20efficient%20in%20an%20office%2C%20where%20they%20could%20collaborate%20more%20easily%20and%20receive%20more%20direct%20training.%20They%20added%20that%20it's%20easier%20to%20build%20trust%20in%20person%2C%20as%20well%20as%20network%20more%20effectively.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBy%20the%20time%20fall%20rolls%20around%2C%20the%20real-estate%20consulting%20firm%20JLL%20predicts%20about%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ffortune.com%2F2023%2F07%2F19%2Fone-million-workers-ordered-return-to-office-fall-2023%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E1%20million%20more%20workers%3C%2Fa%3E%20will%20be%20expected%20to%20return%20at%20least%20part%20time%20to%20the%20office.%20This%20push%20may%20lead%20thousands%20of%20Americans%20to%20look%20for%20work%20at%20more%20flexible%20companies%20to%20avoid%20expensive%20commutes%20and%20childcare.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20tight%20labor%20market%20%E2%80%94%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fjobs-market-hiring-july-unemployment-rate-2023-8%5C%22%3Eunemployment%20rate%20fell%20to%203.5%25%3C%2Fa%3E%20last%20month%2C%20just%20barely%20above%20the%2050-year%20low%20%E2%80%94%20remote%20flexibility%20is%20what%20attracts%20many%20workers.%20In%20a%20survey%20led%20by%20the%20Stanford%20economics%20professor%20Nicholas%20Bloom%2C%20workers%20said%20they%20considered%20flexible%20work%20arrangements%20equivalent%20to%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nber.org%2Fsystem%2Ffiles%2Fworking_papers%2Fw30292%2Fw30292.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eas%20much%20as%20an%208%25%20pay%20raise%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EFully%20in-person%20companies%20underperform%20more%20flexible%20companies%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Scoop%20Technologies%20and%20People%20Data%20Labs%20analysis%20found%20that%20its%20respondents%20that%20were%C2%A0fully%20flexible%20companies%20%E2%80%94%20those%20that%20don't%20require%20any%20days%20in%20the%20office%20%E2%80%94%20grew%20their%20staff%20by%205.6%25%20from%20May%202022%20to%20May%202023.%20This%20figure%20was%20even%20greater%20for%20fully%20remote%20companies%2C%20at%206.9%25.%20That%20last%20number%20was%20over%20double%20the%20head-count%20growth%20rate%20for%20companies%20requiring%20employees%20to%20be%20in%20the%20office%20full%20time%2C%20which%20averaged%202.6%25.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECompany%20respondents%20in%20the%20structured-hybrid%20category%2C%20which%20requires%20some%20days%20in%20the%20office%2C%20grew%20staff%20by%204.1%25%20over%20the%20same%20period%2C%20the%20analysis%20found.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22raw%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%3Ciframe%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdatawrapper.dwcdn.net%2F6mzI9%2F3%2F%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22Growth%20in%20employment%20by%20office%20requirement%5C%22%20data-external%3D%5C%221%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22204%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20study%20found%20the%20average%20company%20requiring%20in-office%20work%20asked%20staff%20to%20come%20in%20just%20over%202.5%20days%20a%20week.%20There%20was%20little%20difference%20between%20companies'%20hiring%20growth%20rates%20for%20those%20requiring%20one%20day%20a%20week%20in%20the%20office%20and%20those%20mandating%20three%20%E2%80%94%20from%20May%202022%20and%20May%202023%2C%20companies%20requiring%20one%20day%20in%20the%20office%20grew%20head%20count%20by%204.8%25%2C%20compared%20with%204.4%25%20for%20those%20requiring%20three%20days%2C%20the%20analysis%20found.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20companies%20have%20been%20pushing%20for%20four-day%20in-person%20workweeks%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdisney-employees-petition-against-working-four-days-in-office-2023-2%5C%22%3Eincluding%20Disney%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20Chipotle.%20Though%20some%20companies%20pushing%20for%20more%20in-person%20requirements%20have%20cited%20reasons%20such%20as%20productivity%2C%20the%20researchers%20found%20a%20decline%20in%20head-count%20growth%20for%20companies%20requiring%20four%20days%20in%20person%2C%20with%20year-over-year%20growth%20at%20just%203.8%25.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BCompany%20executives%20should%20be%20very%20careful%20to%20consider%20the%20potential%20impact%20on%20attracting%20talent%20if%20they%20require%20four%20days%20per%20week%20or%20more%20in%20the%20office%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20report%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThese%20findings%20were%20most%20pronounced%20for%20companies%20with%20between%20500%20and%205%2C000%20employees.%20Over%20the%2012-month%20period%2C%20fully%20flexible%20and%20structured-hybrid%20companies%20grew%20their%20workforce%20by%20more%20than%20double%20the%20rate%20of%20full-time%20in-office%20companies.%20Over%20the%20past%20three%20months%2C%20midsize%20structured-hybrid%20companies%20more%20than%20tripled%20their%20head-count%20growth%20rate%20compared%20with%20fully%20in-person%20companies.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BHeadcount%20growth%20is%20not%20a%20perfect%20proxy%20for%20economic%20growth%2C%20but%20it%20is%20likely%20that%20the%20companies%20that%20are%20adding%20headcount%20are%20also%20the%20ones%20that%20are%20growing%20sales%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20authors%20wrote.%20%26quot%3BPut%20simply%2C%20the%20growth%20in%20the%20economy%20%E2%80%94%20at%20least%20for%20corporate%20employees%20%E2%80%94%20appears%20to%20be%20with%20the%20companies%20that%20are%20offering%20flexibility.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EAre%20you%20a%20business%20owner%20deciding%20on%20your%20work-from-home%20policy%3F%20Have%20you%20found%20difficulty%20hiring%20new%20workers%3F%20Share%20your%20story%20with%20this%20reporter%20at%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22mailto%3Ansheidlower%40insider.com%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ensheidlower%40insider.com%3C%2Fa%3E.%3Cbr%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fremote-jobs-work-from-home-easier-to-hire-2023-8%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1691489701000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64d137bdf5d4870019e358df%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fremote-jobs-work-from-home-easier-to-hire-2023-8%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22New%20data%20indicates%20companies%20with%20remote-work%20options