0exit%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1691488836000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fbsmedia.business-standard.com%2F_media%2Fbs%2Fimg%2Farticle%2F2023-05%2F02%2Ffull%2F1683013227-7789.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Fcompanies%2Fnews%2Fcarlyle-to-acquire-minority-stake-in-quest-global-bain-advent-to-exit-123080800442_1.html%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Ajit%20Prabhu%2C%20chairman%20and%20chief%20executive%20officer%20of%20Quest%20Global%2C%20will%20acquire%20an%20additional%20stake%20in%20the%20company%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Fcompanies%2Fnews%2Fcarlyle-to-acquire-minority-stake-in-quest-global-bain-advent-to-exit-123080800442_1.html%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-business--standard-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Famp%2Fcompanies%2Fnews%2Fcarlyle-to-acquire-minority-stake-in-quest-global-bain-advent-to-exit-123080800442_1.html%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Famp%2Fcompanies%2Fnews%2Fcarlyle-to-acquire-minority-stake-in-quest-global-bain-advent-to-exit-123080800442_1.html%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Banks%20Wrote%20off%20Rs%2014.56%20Lakh%20Crore%20Since%202014-15%3A%20Govt%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2018%2F01%2F24173925%2Fcurrency_pti.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Banks%20have%20written%20off%20bad%20loans%20worth%20Rs%2014.56%20lakh%20crore%20in%20the%20last%20nine%20financial%20years%20starting%202014-15%2C%20parliament%20was%20informed%20on%20Monday%2C%20August%208.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20PTI%2C%20out%20of%20the%20total%20Rs%2014%2C56%2C226%20crore%2C%20written%20off%20loans%20of%20large%20industries%20and%20services%20stood%20at%20Rs%207%2C40%2C968%20crore.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EScheduled%20Commercial%20Banks%20have%20recovered%20an%20aggregate%20amount%20of%20Rs%202%2C04%2C668%20crore%20in%20written-off%20loans%2C%20including%20corporate%20loans%2C%20since%20April%202014%20and%20up%20to%20March%2C%202023%2C%20Minister%20of%20State%20for%20Finance%20Bhagwat%20Karad%20said%20in%20a%20written%20reply%20to%20Lok%20Sabha.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20another%20reply%20by%20the%20minister%2C%20the%20net%20of%20recovery%20in%20written-off%20loans%20during%20the%20financial%20year%20(net%20write-off)%20in%20public%20sector%20banks%20(PSBs)%20was%20Rs%201.18%20lakh%20crore%20in%20the%20FY18%2C%20which%20declined%20to%20Rs%200.91%20lakh%20crore%20in%20FY22%20and%20to%20Rs%200.84%20lakh%20crore%20(RBI%20provisional%20data)%20in%20FY23.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENet%20write-off%20loans%20by%20private%20sector%20banks%20stood%20at%20Rs%2073%2C803%20crore%20(RBI%20provisional%20data)%20in%20FY23%2C%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENet%20write-off%20as%20percentage%20of%20opening%20gross%20loans%20and%20advances%20in%20private%20sector%20banks%20was%201.25%25%20and%201.57%25%20in%20FY18%20and%20FY23%2C%20respectively.%20It%20was%202%25%20and%201.12%25%20for%20PSBs%20during%20the%20same%20period.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20Reserve%20Bank%20of%20India%20(RBI)%2C%20banks%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fbanking%2Fbad-loans-npas-written-off-rbi%5C%22%3Ewrote%20off%3C%2Fa%3E%20non-performing%20assets%20(NPAs)%2C%20or%20bad%20loans%2C%20worth%20over%20Rs%202.09%20lakh%20crore%20(around%20%24%2025.50%20billion)%20during%20the%20year%20ended%20March%202023.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20last%20five%20years%2C%20the%20total%20loan%20write-offs%20by%20the%20banking%20sector%20stood%20at%20Rs%2010.57%20lakh%20crore%2C%20the%20Indian%20Express%20reported%2C%20citing%20an%20RTI%20response%20from%20the%20central%20bank.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20loan%20is%20classified%20as%20an%20NPA%20when%20the%20repayment%20of%20the%20principal%20amount%20or%20the%20interest%20remains%20outstanding%20for%20a%20period%20of%2090%20days.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20measures%20taken%20to%20bring%20down%20bad%20loans%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETo%20support%20asset%20growth%2C%20the%20board%20of%20State%20Bank%20of%20India%20in%20its%20meeting%20held%20on%20June%209%20had%20approved%20raising%20capital%20through%20bonds%2C%20including%20Rs%2020%2C000%20crore%20via%20Basel%20III%20compliant%20AT-1%20bonds%2C%20Rs%2010%2C000%20crore%20via%20Tier-2%20bonds%2C%20and%20Rs%2020%2C000%20crore%20via%20infrastructure%20bonds%20during%20FY24.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20Karad%2C%20banks%20are%20exempted%20from%20maintaining%20cash%20reserve%20ratio%20and%20statutory%20liquidity%20ratio%20on%20long-term%20bonds%20for%20lending%20to%20the%20infrastructure%20sector.%20The%20raising%20of%20long-term%20infrastructure%20bonds%20helps%20the%20bank%20in%20better%20asset%20liability%20management%2C%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAmong%20other%20steps%20to%20bring%20down%20NPAs%2C%20the%20minister%20said%20that%20the%20Securitisation%20and%20Reconstruction%20of%20Financial%20Assets%20and%20Enforcement%20of%20Security%20Interest%20Act%2C%202002%2C%20has%20been%20amended%20to%20make%20it%20more%20effective.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAdditionally%2C%20the%20monetary%20limit%20for%20filing%20cases%20in%20debt%20recovery%20tribunals%20(DRTs)%20was%20increased%20from%20Rs%2010%20lakh%20to%20Rs%2020%20lakh.%20This%20enables%20the%20DRTs%20to%20focus%20on%20high-value%20cases%2C%20resulting%20in%20higher%20recovery%20for%20the%20banks%20and%20financial%20institutions%2C%20the%20minister%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20further%20said%20that%20the%20National%20Asset%20Reconstruction%20Company%20Limited%20(NARCL)%20has%20been%20set%20up%20as%20an%20asset%20reconstruction%20company%20with%20an%20aim%20to%20resolve%20stressed%20assets%20above%20Rs%20500%20crore%20each.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENARCL%20is%20bad%20bank%2C%20which%20buys%20NPAs%2C%20or%20bad%20loans%2C%20from%20banks.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENARCL%20acquired%20three%20borrower%20entities%2C%20including%20Jaypee%20Infratech%2C%20with%20an%20aggregate%20debt%20exposure%20of%20Rs%2021%2C349%20crore%20in%20the%20fourth%20quarter%20of%20FY23%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.financialexpress.com%2Findustry%2Fnarcl-acquires-rs-21349-cr-toxic-assets-far-cry-from-target%2F3185153%2F%5C%22%3Ethe%20%3Cem%3EFinancial%20Express%3C%2Fem%3E%20reported%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20July.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20the%20newspaper%20reported%2C%20%E2%80%9Cthis%20a%20far%20cry%20from%20the%20targets%20set%20for%20transfer%20of%20toxic%20assets%20to%20the%20NARCL.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20October%202021%2C%20the%20NARCL%20got%20a%20licence%20from%20the%20Reserve%20Bank%20of%20India%20to%20start%20operations%2C%20and%20as%20per%20the%20initial%20target%2C%20it%20was%20to%20acquire%20a%20batch%20of%20toxic%20assets%20worth%20about%20Rs%2090%2C000%20crore%20by%20January%202022.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1691488831000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2018%2F01%2F24173925%2Fcurrency_pti.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fbanking%2Fbanks-wrote-off-rs-14-56-lakh-crore-since-2014-15-govt%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Out%20of%20the%20total%20Rs%2014%2C56%2C226%20crore%2C%20written%20off%20loans%20of%20large%20industries%20and%20services%20stood%20at%20Rs%207%2C40%2C968%20crore.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fbanking%2Fbanks-wrote-off-rs-14-56-lakh-crore-since-2014-15-govt%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22AI%20is%20about%20to%20turn%20the%20internet%20into%20a%20total%20nightmare%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222400%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Amid%20an%20orange%20background%2C%20a%20swirl%20of%20fluid%20white%20and%20orange%20lines%20and%20stars%20chaotically%20disrupt%20an%20array%20of%20dark%20blue%20internet%20windows.%20Binary%20code%20decorates%20the%20orange%20background%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64cbf0930f3dff0019568fce%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EAI%20bots%20and%20AI-generated%20content%20are%20flooding%20the%20internet%20with%20spam%2C%20scams%2C%20and%20misinformation.%20And%20it's%20making%20it%20a%20nightmare%20to%20be%20online.%3Cp%3EArantza%20Pena%20Popo%2FInsider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20logging%20on%20to%20HBO%20Max%20at%20the%20end%20of%20May%2C%20people%20noticed%20something%20strange.%C2%A0%20Usually%20when%20someone%20logs%20into%20the%20site%2C%20HBO%20asks%20them%20to%20verify%20that%20they%20are%20human%20by%20solving%20a%20captcha%20%E2%80%94%20you%20know%2C%20the%20little%20%26quot%3BI%20am%20not%20a%20robot%26quot%3B%20checkbox%20or%20the%20%26quot%3Bselect%20all%20squares%20with%20stoplights%26quot%3B%20image%20grids%20that%20prove%20to%20the%20website%20that%20you%20are%2C%20in%20fact%2C%20a%20human.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20this%20time%2C%20when%20users%20logged%20on%20they%20were%20asked%20to%20solve%20a%20complex%20series%20of%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.entrepreneur.com%2Fbusiness-news%2Fuser-slam-max-app-for-impossible-captcha-login-tests%2F453418%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epuzzles%3C%2Fa%3E%20instead.%20The%20bizarre%20tasks%20ranged%20from%20adding%20up%20the%20dots%20on%20images%20of%20dice%20to%20listening%20to%20short%20audio%20clips%20and%20selecting%20the%20clip%20that%20contained%20a%20repeating%20sound%20pattern.%20These%20odd%20new%20tasks%2C%20ostensibly%20to%20prove%20users%20were%20human%2C%20haven't%20been%20limited%20to%20HBO%3A%20Across%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.vice.com%2Fen%2Farticle%2Fxgwy5n%2Fcaptcha-is-asking-users-to-identify-objects-that-dont-exist%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eplatforms%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20users%20have%20been%20stumped%20by%20increasingly%20impossible%20puzzles%20like%20identifying%20objects%20%E2%80%94%20such%20as%20a%20horse%20made%20out%20of%20clouds%20%E2%80%94%20that%20do%20not%20exist.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20reason%20behind%20these%20new%20hoops%3F%20Improved%20AI.%20Since%20tech%20companies%20have%20trained%20their%20bots%20on%20the%20older%20captchas%2C%20these%20programs%20are%20now%20so%20capable%20that%20they%20can%20easily%20beat%20typical%20challenges.%20As%20a%20result%2C%20we%20humans%20have%20to%20put%20more%20effort%20into%20proving%20our%20humanness%20just%20to%20get%20online.%20But%20head-scratching%20captchas%20are%20just%20the%20tip%20of%20the%20iceberg%20when%20it%20comes%20to%20how%20AI%20is%20rewriting%20the%20mechanics%20of%20the%20internet.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESince%20the%20arrival%20of%20ChatGPT%20last%20year%2C%20tech%20companies%20have%20raced%20to%20incorporate%20the%20AI%20tech%20behind%20it.%20In%20many%20cases%2C%20companies%20have%20uprooted%20their%20long-standing%20core%20products%20to%20do%20so.%20The%20ease%20of%20producing%20seemingly%20authoritative%20text%20and%20visuals%20with%20a%20click%20of%20a%20button%20threatens%20to%20erode%20the%20internet's%20fragile%20institutions%20and%20make%20navigating%20the%20web%20a%20morass%20of%20confusion.%20As%20AI%20fever%20has%20taken%20hold%20of%20the%20web%2C%20researchers%20have%20unearthed%20how%20it%20can%20be%20weaponized%20to%20aggravate%20some%20of%20the%20internet's%20most%20pressing%20concerns%20%E2%80%94%20like%20misinformation%20and%20privacy%20%E2%80%94%20while%20also%20making%20the%20simple%20day-to-day%20experience%20of%20being%20online%20%E2%80%94%20from%20deleting%20spam%20to%20just%20logging%20into%20sites%20%E2%80%94%20more%20annoying%20than%20it%20already%20is.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BNot%20to%20say%20that%20our%20inability%20to%20rein%20AI%20in%20will%20lead%20to%20the%20collapse%20of%20society%2C%26quot%3B%20Christian%20Selig%2C%20the%20creator%20of%20Apollo%2C%20a%20popular%20Reddit%20app%2C%20told%20me%2C%20%26quot%3Bbut%20I%20think%20it%20certainly%20has%20the%20potential%20to%20profoundly%20affect%20the%20internet.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20so%20far%2C%20AI%20is%20making%20the%20internet%20a%20nightmare.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EInternet%20disruption%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20close%20to%2020%20years%2C%20Reddit%20has%20been%20the%20internet's%20unofficial%20front%20page%2C%20and%20that%20longevity%20is%20due%20in%20large%20part%20to%20the%20volunteers%20who%20moderate%20its%20various%20communities.%20By%20one%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.northwestern.edu%2Fstories%2F2022%2F05%2Funpaid-social-media-moderators%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eestimate%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Reddit%20moderators%20do%20%243.4%20million%20worth%20of%20annual%20unpaid%20work.%20To%20do%20this%2C%20they%20rely%20on%20tools%20like%20Apollo%2C%20a%20near-decade-old%20app%20that%20offers%20advanced%20moderation%20tools.%20But%20in%20June%2C%20users%20were%20greeted%20with%20an%20unusual%20message%3A%20Apollo%20was%20shutting%20down.%20In%20the%20company's%20attempt%20to%20get%20in%20on%20the%20AI%20gold%20rush%2C%20third-party%20apps%20faced%20the%20chopping%20block.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EApollo%20and%20other%20interfaces%20like%20it%20rely%20on%20access%20to%20Reddit's%20application%20programming%20interface%2C%20or%20API%2C%20a%20piece%20of%20software%20that%20helps%20apps%20exchange%20data.%20In%20the%20past%2C%20Reddit%20allowed%20anyone%20to%20scrape%20its%20data%20for%20free%20%E2%80%94%20the%20more%20tools%20Reddit%20allowed%2C%20the%20more%20users%20it%20attracted%2C%20which%20helped%20the%20app%20grow.%20But%20now%2C%20AI%20companies%20have%20begun%20to%20use%20Reddit%20and%20its%20vast%20reserve%20of%20online%20human%20interaction%20to%20train%20their%20models.%20In%20an%20attempt%20to%20cash%20in%20on%20this%20sudden%20interest%2C%20Reddit%20announced%20new%2C%20expensive%20pricing%20for%20access%20to%20its%20data.%20Apollo%20and%20other%20apps%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Freddit-client-apollo-shut-down-after-talks-got-ugly-2023-6%5C%22%3Ebecame%20collateral%20damage%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20sparking%20a%20month%20of%20protests%20and%20unrest%20from%20the%20Reddit%20community.%20The%20company%20refused%20to%20budge%2C%20even%20though%20that%20meant%20alienating%20the%20communities%20of%20people%20who%20make%20up%20its%20soul.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cblockquote%3E%3Cq%3EA%20report%20from%20Europol%20expects%20a%20mind-blowing%2090%25%20of%20internet%20content%20to%20be%20AI-generated%20in%20a%20few%20years.%3C%2Fq%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20data-scraping%20cash%20cows%20undermine%20the%20quality%20of%20once-reliable%20sites%2C%20a%20glut%20of%20questionable%20AI-generated%20content%20is%20spilling%20out%20over%20the%20pages%20of%20the%20web.%20Martijn%20Pieters%2C%20a%20Cambridge-based%20software%20engineer%2C%20recently%20witnessed%20the%20decline%20of%20Stack%20Overflow%2C%20the%20internet's%20go-to%20website%20for%20technical%20questions%20and%20answers.%20He'd%20been%20contributing%20to%20and%20moderating%20on%20the%20platform%20for%20over%20a%20decade%20when%20it%20took%20a%20sudden%20nosedive%20in%20June.%20The%20company%20behind%20the%20site%2C%20Prosus%2C%20decided%20to%20allow%20AI-generated%20answers%20and%20began%20charging%20AI%20firms%20for%20access%20to%20its%20data.%20In%20response%2C%20top%20moderators%20went%20on%20strike%2C%20arguing%20that%20the%20low-quality%20AI-generated%20content%20went%20against%20the%20very%20purpose%20of%20the%20site%3A%20%26quot%3BTo%20be%20a%20repository%20of%20high-quality%20question%20and%20answer%20content.%26quot%3B%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENewsGuard%2C%20a%20firm%20that%20tracks%20misinformation%20and%20rates%20the%20credibility%20of%20information%20websites%2C%20has%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.newsguardtech.com%2Fspecial-reports%2Fai-tracking-center%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efound%3C%2Fa%3E%20close%20to%20350%20online%20news%20outlets%20that%20are%20almost%20entirely%20generated%20by%20AI%20with%20little%20to%20no%20human%20oversight.%20Sites%20such%20as%20Biz%20Breaking%20News%20and%20Market%20News%20Reports%20churn%20out%20generic%20articles%20spanning%20a%20range%20of%20subjects%2C%20including%20politics%2C%20tech%2C%20economics%2C%20and%20travel.%20Many%20of%20these%20articles%20are%20rife%20with%20unverified%20claims%2C%20conspiracy%20theories%2C%20and%20hoaxes.%20When%20NewsGuard%20tested%20the%20AI%20model%20behind%20ChatGPT%20to%20gauge%20its%20tendency%20to%20spread%20false%20narratives%2C%20it%20failed%20100%20out%20of%20100%20times.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAI%20frequently%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-chatbots-chatgpt-google-bard-microsoft-bing-break-internet-search-2023-2%5C%22%3Ehallucinates%3C%2Fa%3E%20answers%20to%20questions%2C%20and%20unless%20the%20AI%20models%20are%20fine-tuned%20and%20protected%20with%20guardrails%2C%20Gordon%20Crovitz%2C%20NewsGuard's%20co-CEO%20told%20me%2C%20%26quot%3Bthey%20will%20be%20the%20greatest%20source%20of%20persuasive%20misinformation%20at%20scale%20in%20the%20history%20of%20the%20internet.%26quot%3B%20A%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ffuturism.com%2Fthe-byte%2Fexperts-90-online-content-ai-generated%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ereport%3C%2Fa%3E%20from%20Europol%2C%20the%20European%20Union's%20law-enforcement%20agency%2C%20expects%20a%20mind-blowing%2090%25%20of%20internet%20content%20to%20be%20AI-generated%20in%20a%20few%20years.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThough%20these%20AI-generated%20news%20websites%20don't%20have%20a%20significant%20audience%20yet%2C%20their%20rapid%20rise%20is%20a%20precursor%20to%20how%20easily%20AI-generated%20content%20will%20distort%20information%20on%20social%20media.%20In%20his%20research%2C%20Filippo%20Menczer%2C%20a%20computer%20science%20professor%20and%20director%20of%20Indiana%20University's%20Observatory%20on%20Social%20Media%2C%20has%20already%20found%20networks%20of%20bots%20that%20are%20posting%20large%20volumes%20of%20ChatGPT-generated%20content%20to%20social-media%20sites%20like%20X%20(formerly%20Twitter)%20and%20Facebook.%20And%20while%20AI%20bots%20have%20telltale%20signs%20now%2C%20experts%20indicate%20that%20they%20will%20soon%20get%20better%20at%20mimicking%20humans%20and%20evading%20the%20detection%20systems%20developed%20by%20Menczer%20and%20social%20networks.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20user-run%20sites%20like%20Reddit%20and%20social-media%20platforms%20are%20always%20fighting%20back%20against%20bad%20actors%2C%20people%20are%20also%20losing%20a%20crucial%20place%20they%20turn%20to%20to%20verify%20information%3A%20search%20engines.%20Microsoft%20and%20Google%20will%20soon%20bury%20traditional%20search-result%20links%20in%20favor%20of%20summaries%20stitched%20together%20by%20bots%20that%20are%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgoogle-search-boss-warns-ai-can-give-fictitious-answers-report-2023-2%5C%22%3Eill-equipped%20to%20distinguish%20fact%20from%20fiction.%3C%2Fa%3E%20When%20we%20search%20a%20query%20on%20Google%2C%20we%20not%20only%20learn%20the%20answer%2C%20but%20also%20how%20it%20fits%20in%20the%20broader%20context%20of%20what's%20on%20the%20internet.%20We%20filter%20those%20results%20and%20then%20choose%20the%20sources%20we%20trust.%20A%20chatbot-powered%20search%20engine%20cuts%20off%20these%20experiences%2C%20strips%20context%20like%20website%20addresses%2C%20and%20can%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdl.acm.org%2Fdoi%2F10.1145%2F3442188.3445922%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eparrot%3C%2Fa%3E%26quot%3B%20a%20plagiarized%20answer%2C%20which%20NewsGuard's%20Crovitz%20told%20me%20sounds%20%26quot%3Bauthoritative%2C%20well-written%2C%26quot%3B%20but%20is%20%26quot%3Bentirely%20false.%26quot%3B%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESynthetic%20content%20has%20also%20swamped%20e-commerce%20platforms%20like%20Amazon%20and%20Etsy.%20Two%20weeks%20before%20a%20technical%20textbook%20from%20Christopher%20Cowell%2C%20a%20curriculum%20engineer%20from%20Portland%2C%20Oregon%2C%20was%20set%20to%20be%20published%2C%20he%20discovered%20a%20newly%20listed%20book%20with%20the%20same%20title%20on%20Amazon.%20Cowell%20soon%20realized%20it%20was%20AI-generated%20and%20the%20publisher%20behind%20it%20likely%20picked%20up%20the%20title%20from%20Amazon's%20prerelease%20list%20and%20fed%20it%20into%20software%20like%20ChatGPT.%20Similarly%2C%20on%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2Ftheatlantic.com%2Ftechnology%2Farchive%2F2023%2F06%2Fai-chatgpt-side-hustle%2F674415%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EEtsy%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20platform%20known%20for%20its%20hand-crafted%2C%20artisanal%20catalog%2C%20AI-generated%20art%2C%20mugs%2C%20and%20books%20are%20now%20commonplace.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20other%20words%2C%20it's%20going%20to%20quickly%20become%20very%20difficult%20to%20distinguish%20what's%20real%20from%20what's%20not%20online.%20While%20misinformation%20has%20long%20been%20a%20problem%20with%20the%20internet%2C%20AI%20is%20going%20to%20blow%20our%20old%20problems%20out%20of%20the%20water.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EA%20scamming%20bonanza%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20short%20term%2C%20AI's%20rise%20will%20introduce%20a%20host%20of%20tangible%20security%20and%20privacy%20challenges.%20Online%20scams%2C%20which%20have%20been%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fresources.sift.com%2Febook%2Fq2-2023-digital-trust-safety-index-ai-and-automation%2F%3F_gl%3D1*1wv15su*_ga*Nzk2OTIyNTY4LjE2ODk5NDIxNzY.*_ga_R8SV2EK5NZ*MTY4OTk0MjE3Ni4xLjAuMTY4OTk0MjE3Ni42MC4wLjA.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Egrowing%20since%20November%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20will%20be%20harder%20to%20detect%20because%20AI%20will%20make%20them%20easier%20to%20tailor%20to%20each%20target.%20Research%20conducted%20by%20John%20Licato%2C%20a%20computer%20science%20professor%20at%20the%20University%20of%20South%20Florida%2C%20has%20found%20that%20it's%20possible%20to%20accurately%20engineer%20scams%20down%20to%20an%20individual's%20preferences%20and%20behavioral%20tendencies%20given%20very%20little%20information%20about%20a%20person%20from%20public%20websites%20and%20social-media%20profiles.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20of%20the%20key%20telltale%20signs%20of%20high-risk%20phishing%20scams%20%E2%80%94%20a%20kind%20of%20attack%20where%20the%20intruder%20masquerades%20as%20a%20trusted%20entity%20like%20your%20bank%20to%20steal%20sensitive%20information%20%E2%80%94%20is%20that%20the%20text%20often%20contains%20typos%20or%20the%20graphics%20aren't%20as%20refined%20and%20clear%20as%20they%20should%20be.%20But%20these%20signs%20won't%20exist%20in%20an%20AI-powered%20fraud%20network%2C%20with%20hackers%20turning%20free%20text-to-image%20and%20text%20generators%20like%20ChatGPT%20into%20powerful%20spam%20engines.%20Generative%20AI%20could%20potentially%20be%20used%20to%20plaster%20your%20profile%20picture%20in%20a%20brand's%20personalized%20email%20campaign%20or%20produce%20a%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theverge.com%2F2020%2F2%2F18%2F21142782%2Findia-politician-deepfakes-ai-elections%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Evideo%20message%20from%20a%20politician%20with%20an%20artificially%20reworked%20voice%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20speaking%20exclusively%20on%20the%20topics%20you%20care%20about.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cblockquote%3E%3Cq%3EThe%20internet%20will%20increasingly%20feel%20like%20it's%20engineered%20for%20the%20machines%20and%20by%20the%20machines.%3C%2Fq%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20this%20is%20already%20happening%3A%20Data%20from%20a%20cybersecurity%20firm%2C%20Darktrace%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdarktrace.com%2Fresources%2Fgenerative-ai-impact-on-email-cyber-attacks%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edetected%3C%2Fa%3E%20a%20135%25%20increase%20in%20malicious%20cyber%20campaigns%20since%20the%20start%20of%202023%2C%20and%20revealed%20criminals%20are%20increasingly%20turning%20to%20bots%20to%20write%20phishing%20emails%20to%20send%20error-free%2C%20longer%20messages%20that%20are%20less%20likely%20to%20be%20caught%20by%20spam%20filters.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20soon%20hackers%20may%20not%20have%20to%20go%20through%20too%20much%20trouble%20to%20obtain%20your%20sensitive%20information.%20Right%20now%2C%20hackers%20often%20resort%20to%20a%20maze%20of%20indirect%20methods%20to%20spy%20on%20you%2C%20including%20hidden%20trackers%20inside%20websites%20and%20buying%20large%20datasets%20of%20compromised%20information%20off%20of%20the%20dark%20web.%20But%20security%20researchers%20have%20discovered%20that%20the%20AI%20bots%20in%20your%20apps%20and%20devices%20might%20steal%20sensitive%20information%20for%20the%20hackers.%20Since%20AI%20models%20from%20OpenAI%20and%20Google%20actively%20crawl%20the%20web%2C%20hackers%20can%20hide%20malicious%20codes%20%E2%80%94%20a%20set%20of%20instructions%20for%20the%20bot%20%E2%80%94%20inside%20websites%20and%20make%20the%20bots%20execute%20it%20with%20no%20human%20intervention.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESay%20you're%20on%20Microsoft%20Edge%2C%20a%20browser%20that%20comes%20built-in%20with%20the%20Bing%20AI%20chatbot.%20Because%20the%20chatbot%20is%20constantly%20reading%20the%20pages%20you%20look%20at%2C%20it%20could%20pick%20up%20malicious%20code%20concealed%20in%20a%20website%20you%20visit.%20The%20code%20could%20ask%20Bing%20AI%20to%20pretend%20to%20be%20a%20Microsoft%20employee%2C%20prompt%20you%20with%20a%20new%20offer%20to%20use%20Microsoft%20Office%20for%20free%2C%20and%20ask%20for%20your%20credit-card%20details.%20That's%20how%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fgreshake.github.io%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eone%20security%20expert%20managed%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20trick%20Bing%20AI.%20Florian%20Tram%C3%A8r%2C%20an%20assistant%20professor%20of%20computer%20science%20at%20ETH%20Z%C3%BCrich%2C%20finds%20these%20%26quot%3Bprompt%20injection%26quot%3B%20attacks%20concerning%2C%20especially%20considering%20AI%20smart%20assistants%20are%20making%20their%20way%20into%20all%20sorts%20of%20apps%20such%20as%20email%20inboxes%2C%20browsers%2C%20office%20software%2C%20and%20more%2C%20and%20therefore%2C%20can%20easily%20access%20data.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSomething%20like%20a%20smart%20AI%20assistant%20that%20manages%20your%20email%2C%20calendar%2C%20purchases%2C%20etc.%2C%20is%20just%20not%20viable%20at%20the%20moment%20because%20of%20these%20risks%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Tram%C3%A8r.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E'Dead%20internet'%C2%A0%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20AI%20continues%20to%20wreak%20havoc%20on%20community-led%20initiatives%20like%20Wikipedia%20and%20Reddit%2C%20the%20internet%20will%20increasingly%20feel%20like%20it's%20engineered%20for%20the%20machines%20and%20by%20the%20machines.%20That%20could%20break%20the%20web%20we're%20used%20to%20now%2C%20Toby%20Walsh%2C%20an%20artificial%20intelligence%20professor%20at%20the%20University%20of%20New%20South%20Wales%2C%20told%20me.%20It%20will%20also%20make%20things%20difficult%20for%20the%20AI%20makers%20as%20well.%20As%20AI-generated%20content%20drowns%20out%20human%20work%2C%20tech%20companies%20like%20Microsoft%20and%20Google%20will%20have%20less%20original%20data%20to%20improve%20their%20models.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAI%20today%20works%20because%20it%20is%20trained%20on%20the%20sweat%20and%20ingenuity%20of%20humans%2C%26quot%3B%20Walsh%20said.%20%26quot%3BIf%20the%20second-gen%20generative%20AI%20is%20trained%20on%20the%20exhaust%20of%20the%20first%20generation%2C%20the%20quality%20will%20drop%20drastically.%26quot%3B%20Earlier%20this%20year%20in%20May%2C%20a%20University%20of%20Oxford%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Farxiv.org%2Fpdf%2F2305.17493v2.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Estudy%3C%2Fa%3E%20found%20that%20training%20AI%20on%20data%20generated%20by%20other%20AI%20systems%20causes%20it%20to%20degrade%20and%20ultimately%20collapse.%20And%20as%20it%20does%2C%20so%20will%20the%20quality%20of%20information%20found%20online.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELicato%2C%20the%20University%20of%20South%20Florida%20professor%2C%20likens%20the%20current%20state%20of%20the%20web%20experience%20to%20the%20%26quot%3Bdead%20internet%26quot%3B%20theory.%20As%20the%20internet's%20most-visited%20sites%20like%20Reddit%20become%20flooded%20with%20bot-written%20articles%20and%20comments%2C%20companies%20will%20deploy%20additional%20counter-bots%20to%20read%20and%20filter%20automated%20content.%20Eventually%2C%20the%20theory%20goes%2C%20most%20of%20the%20content%20creation%20and%20consumption%20on%20the%20internet%20will%20no%20longer%20be%20done%20by%20humans.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20a%20weird%20thing%20to%20imagine%2C%20but%20it%20seems%20increasingly%20likely%20with%20how%20things%20are%20going%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Licato.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20can't%20help%20but%20agree.%20Over%20the%20past%20few%20months%2C%20the%20places%20I%20used%20to%20frequent%20online%20are%20either%20overrun%20with%20AI-generated%20content%20and%20faces%20or%20are%20so%20occupied%20with%20keeping%20up%20with%20their%20rivals'%20AI%20updates%20that%20they've%20crippled%20their%20core%20services.%20If%20it%20goes%20on%2C%20the%20internet%20will%20never%20be%20the%20same%20again.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%3Ca%20data-mrf-link%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fauthor%2Fshubham-agarwal%5C%22%20rel%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20data-uri%3D%5C%22d6d846ef1e7d832abbabfa4f3180a7dc%5C%22%20data-analytics-module%3D%5C%22body_link%5C%22%20data-analytics-post-depth%3D%5C%22100%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fauthor%2Fshubham-agarwal%5C%22%20data-analytics-product-module%3D%5C%22body_link%5C%22%3EShubham%20Agarwal%3C%2Fa%3E%C