Their%20drafts%20should%20have%20been%20made%20public%2C%20Aziz%20told%20%3Cem%3EDW%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20adding%20that%20there%20was%20no%20transparency%20during%20the%20entire%20legislative%20process.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CParliamentarians%20did%20not%20have%20any%20effective%20debate%20over%20the%20Bills.%20They%20did%20consult%20some%20stakeholders%20but%20we%20were%20not%20informed%20about%20the%20input%20that%20we%20offered%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAziz%20believes%20the%20government%20wants%20total%20control%20over%20social%20media.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CAnd%20these%20Bills%20have%20been%20passed%20to%20control%20social%20media%2C%E2%80%9D%20Aziz%20said.%20%E2%80%9CNow%20it%20will%20be%20up%20to%20the%20government%20as%20to%20what%20it%20allows%20to%20be%20uploaded%20and%20what%20it%20wants%20to%20be%20removed.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EPress%20freedom%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPakistani%20journalists%20have%20raised%20concerns%20about%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dw.com%2Fen%2Frsf-amnesty-ask-pakistan-to-find-pro-khan-anchor-imran-riaz%2Fa-65709589%5C%22%3Epress%20freedom%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0following%20the%20amendments%20to%20cybercrime%20legislation%2C%20as%20they%20and%20their%20colleagues%20had%20previously%20unearthed%20corruption%20scandals%20after%20receiving%20information%20from%20government%20institutions%20through%20their%20sources.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAfter%20the%20passage%20of%20these%20laws%2C%20it%20will%20be%20very%20difficult%20for%20media%20representatives%20to%20obtain%20information%20or%20documents%20such%20as%C2%A0copies%20from%20government%20departments%20as%C2%A0Farzana%20Ali%2C%20a%20Peshawar-based%20journalist%2C%20told%20%3Cem%3EDW%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20adding%20this%20would%20prevent%20journalists%20from%20being%20able%20to%20back%C2%A0claims%20of%20corruption%20or%20malpractice.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CAfter%20the%20passage%20of%20this%20law%2C%20the%C2%A0Right%20to%20Information%20Act%20becomes%20pointless%2C%20because%20if%20government%20departments%20cannot%20pass%20information%20to%20media%20persons%2C%20what%20is%20the%20use%3F%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20Ali.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20article%20was%20originally%20published%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dw.com%2Fen%2Ftop-stories%2Fs-9097%5C%22%3EDW.%C2%A0%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1691480170000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F01%2F24215513%2F6483091829_b0a9599ab5_k.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fsouth-asia%2Fpakistan-rights-groups-slam-pro-military-legislation%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Activists%20and%20politicians%20have%20slammed%20several%20Bills%20that%20were%20recently%20passed%20in%20Pakistan%20ahead%20of%20general%20elections.%20Many%20lawmakers%20say%20that%20some%20of%20them%20were%20approved%20in%20haste%20and%20bypassed%20democratic%20norms.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fsouth-asia%2Fpakistan-rights-groups-slam-pro-military-legislation%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Kalakshetra%3A%20Panel%20Finds%20Hari%20Padman%20Guilty%20of%20Sexual%20Harassment%2C%20Suggests%20'Major%20Punishment'%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F04%2F03120557%2FHari-Padman.jpeg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Sexual%20harassment%20accused%20professor%20Hari%20Padman%20has%20been%20found%20guilty%20by%20the%20independent%20inquiry%20committee%20constituted%20by%20the%20Kalakshetra%20Foundation%2C%20the%20%3Cem%3EHindu%3C%2Fem%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thehindu.com%2Fnews%2Fnational%2Ftamil-nadu%2Fkalakshetra-inquiry-panel-calls-hari-padman-a-delinquent-submits-its-report%2Farticle67168371.ece%5C%22%3Ereported%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20thre