de-ex-india-stars-bold-claim-4278703%2Famp%2F1%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Flight%20of%20Personal%20Capital%20Under%20LRS%20May%20Exceed%20Inbound%20FDI%20This%20Year%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F08121321%2FUntitled-design-3.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3EThe%C2%A0%3Cem%3EEconomic%20Times%3C%2Fem%3E%C2%A0has%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fm.economictimes.com%2Fnri%2Finvest%2Fresident-indians-frontload-lrs-spends%2Farticleshow%2F102253956.cms%5C%22%3Ereported%3C%2Fa%3E%20a%20massive%20surge%20in%20the%20outflow%20of%20dollars%20in%20May%20under%20the%20Liberalised%20Remittance%20Scheme%20(LRS)%20window%20of%20the%20Reserve%20Bank%20of%20India%2C%20which%20allows%20Indians%20to%20take%20up%20to%20%242%2C50%2C000%20out%20of%20the%20country%20every%20year.%20May%20saw%20a%2040%25%20year%20on%20year%20increase%20in%20the%20outflow%2C%20which%20reached%20%242.9%20billion.%20Such%20a%20big%20surge%20in%20dollar%20outflows%20via%20the%20LRS%20window%20has%20been%20worrying%20the%20government%20no%20end.%20In%202022-23%20the%20total%20forex%20outflow%20under%20the%20LRS%20window%20was%20close%20to%20%2428%20billion%2C%20nearly%20a%2030%25%20increase%20over%20the%20previous%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGoing%20by%20the%20May%20outflow%20figure%20of%C2%A0%20%242.9%20billion%2C%20this%20year%20the%20annual%20number%20may%20well%20exceed%20%2435%20billion.%20For%20the%20sake%20of%20comparison%2C%20it%20must%20be%20noted%20that%20total%20outflows%20effected%20by%20individuals%20via%20the%20LRS%20window%20was%20only%20%241.3%20billion%20in%202014-15%2C%20the%20year%20Modi%20took%20over%20as%20Prime%20Minister.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThese%20are%20the%20annual%20LRS%20outgo%20figures%20(in%20%24%20million)%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ctable%3E%5Cn%3Ctbody%3E%5Cn%3Ctr%3E%5Cn%3Ctd%3E2013-14%3C%2Ftd%3E%5Cn%3Ctd%3E1039.8%3C%2Ftd%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ftr%3E%5Cn%3Ctr%3E%5Cn%3Ctd%3E2014-15%3C%2Ftd%3E%5Cn%3Ctd%3E1325.8%3C%2Ftd%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ftr%3E%5Cn%3Ctr%3E%5Cn%3Ctd%3E2015-16%3C%2Ftd%3E%5Cn%3Ctd%3E4642.6%3C%2Ftd%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ftr%3E%5Cn%3Ctr%3E%5Cn%3Ctd%3E2016-17%3C%2Ftd%3E%5Cn%3Ctd%3E8170%3C%2Ftd%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ftr%3E%5Cn%3Ctr%3E%5Cn%3Ctd%3E2017-18%3C%2Ftd%3E%5Cn%3Ctd%3E11%2C333.6%3C%2Ftd%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ftr%3E%5Cn%3Ctr%3E%5Cn%3Ctd%3E2018-19%3C%2Ftd%3E%5Cn%3Ctd%3E13%2C787.6%3C%2Ftd%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ftr%3E%5Cn%3Ctr%3E%5Cn%3Ctd%3E2019-20%3C%2Ftd%3E%5Cn%3Ctd%3E18760.69%3C%2Ftd%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ftr%3E%5Cn%3Ctr%3E%5Cn%3Ctd%3E2020-21%3C%2Ftd%3E%5Cn%3Ctd%3E12%2C684.4%3C%2Ftd%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ftr%3E%5Cn%3Ctr%3E%5Cn%3Ctd%3E2021-22%3C%2Ftd%3E%5Cn%3Ctd%3E19610.77%3C%2Ftd%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ftr%3E%5Cn%3Ctr%3E%5Cn%3Ctd%3E2022-23%3C%2Ftd%3E%5Cn%3Ctd%3E27%2C140.65%3C%2Ftd%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ftr%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ftbody%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ftable%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20scale%20of%20increase%20in%20the%20outgo%20since%202014-15%20is%20a%20bit%20of%20a%20puzzle.%20The%20%2428%20billion%20outflow%20in%202022-23%20is%2C%20incidentally%2C%20equal%20to%20the%20net%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Feconomy%2Fprecipitous-decline-fdi-last-two-years-modi-tenure%5C%22%3EFDI%20inflow%3C%2Fa%3E%20into%C2%A0%3Cspan%3EIndia%3C%2Fspan%3E%C2%A0in%20the%20same%20period!%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20does%20seem%20a%20bit%20odd%20that%20money%20taken%20out%20by%20individuals%20via%20the%20RBI%E2%80%99s%20LRS%20window%20should%20be%20as%20much%20or%20more%20than%20net%20FDI%20inflows.%20In%20the%20current%20fiscal%2C%20the%20LRS%20outflows%20could%20exceed%20net%20FDI%20inflows.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20is%20worrying%20the%20government%2C%20which%20recently%20tried%20to%20levy%20a%2020%25%20tax%20at%20source%20on%20all%20LRS%20remittances%20by%20individuals%20above%20a%20limit%20of%20Rs%207%20lakh.%20The%20tax%20levy%20was%20postponed%20to%20October%20because%20banks%20were%20not%20ready%20with%20systems%20to%20monitor%20the%20LRS%20scheme%20closely.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20government%20seems%20to%20assume%20that%2050%25%20of%20the%20total%20remittances%20are%20travel-related.%20Money%20is%20also%20taken%20out%20by%20individuals%20to%20educate%20their%20children%20abroad.%20This%20constitutes%20less%20than%20%242%20billion%20of%20the%20annual%20LRS%20outgo.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20appears%20that%20the%20travel-related%20outflow%20of%20about%20%2414%20billion%20in%202022-23%20hides%20other%20expenses%20linked%20to%20the%20number%20of%20Indian%20millionaires%20who%20have%20taken%20residency%20abroad%20since%202014-15.%20On%20average%2C%206%2C500-7%2C000%20millionaires%20have%20left%20the%20country%20every%20year%20since%202014-15%2C%20the%20year%20Modi%20came%20to%20power.%20This%20marks%20a%20roughly%2050%25%20increase%20in%20the%20annual%20exodus%2C%20compared%20to%20the%20period%20before%202014-15.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESome%20analysts%20say%20that%20every%20other%20small%20and%20medium%20scale%20business%20family%20is%20hedging%20by%20sending%20one%20or%20two%20members%20abroad%20to%20take%20residency.%20This%20could%20have%20led%20to%20a%20significant%C2%A0%20increase%20in%20associated%20expenditures%20like%20buying%20property%20abroad%2C%20spending%20on%20maintenance%20of%20a%20home%20and%20other%20investments%20in%20equity%20and%20deposits.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20has%20also%20contributed%20to%20the%20unprecedented%20surge%20in%20the%20forex%20outflows%20via%20the%20LRS%20window%20in%20recent%20years.%20This%20is%20likely%20to%20continue%20even%20if%20a%2020%25%20tax%20at%20source%20is%20imposed%2C%20which%20is%20in%20any%20case%20refundable.%20The%20RBI%20data%C2%A0%20indicates%20that%2080%25%20of%20the%20LRS%20outflow%20comprises%20travel%2C%20property%20and%20equity%20purchases%20abroad%2C%20and%20gifts%20and%20maintenance%20expenses%20for%20staying%20abroad.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20sum%2C%20the%20surge%20in%20the%20LRS%20outflow%20has%20something%20to%20do%20with%20rich%20Indians%20who%20want%20to%20park%20some%20money%20and%20investments%20outside%20Indian%20territory%2C%20fearing%20this%20regime%E2%80%99s%20arbitrary%20enforcement%20and%20tax%20policies.%20The%20magnitude%20of%20outflows%20is%20not%20explained%20by%20a%20post-Covid%20surge%20in%20tourist%20travel%20alone.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20trend%20is%20clear%3A%20LRS%20outflows%20were%20increasing%20massively%20even%20before%20the%20COVID-19%20period%2C%20from%202014-15%20to%202019-20.%20Indians%20tourists%20couldn%E2%80%99t%20have%20started%20travelling%20a%20lot%20more%20after%20Modi%20came%20to%20power.%20The%20surge%20cannot%20be%20explained%20by%20outward%20tourism%20alone.%20There%20is%20something%20else%20happening%20which%20calls%20for%20deeper%20inspection.%20It%20is%20not%20normal%20that%20the%20individuals%20taking%20money%20abroad%20via%20a%20special%20window%20exceeds%20the%20net%20FDI%20inflows%2C%20which%20is%20a%20distinct%20possibility%20in%20this%20fiscal%20year!%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20piece%20was%20first%20published%20on%20The%20India%20Cable%20%E2%80%93%20a%20premium%20newsletter%20from%20The%20Wire%20%26amp%3B%20Galileo%20Ideas%20%E2%80%93%20and%20has%20been%20republished%20here.%20To%20subscribe%20to%20The%20India%20Cable%2C%20click%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheindiacable.com%2F%5C%22%3Ehere%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1691477160000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F08121321%2FUntitled-design-3.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Feconomy%2Fpersonal-capital-lrs-fdi%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20trend%20is%20clear%3A%20LRS%20outflows%20were%20increasing%20massively%20even%20before%20the%20COVID-19%20period%2C%20from%202014-15%20to%202019-20.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Feconomy%2Fpersonal-capital-lrs-fdi%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22William%20Friedkin%2C%20Director%20of%20%E2%80%98The%20Exorcist%2C%E2%80%99%20Dies%20at%2087%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F08105051%2FUntitled-design-3.png%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3EWilliam%20Friedkin%2C%20the%20American%20director%20behind%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dw.com%2Fen%2Facting-legend-max-von-sydow-dies-aged-90%2Fa-52692790%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EThe%20Exorcist%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%3C%2Fa%3E%20died%20on%20Monday.%20He%20was%2087.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFriedkin%20passed%20away%20in%20Los%20Angeles%20after%20suffering%20unspecified%20health%20issues%20in%20recent%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20had%20%E2%80%9Cbeen%20working%20until%20a%20few%20weeks%20ago%E2%80%9D%20but%20%E2%80%9Chad%20been%20in%20declining%20health%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20former%20%3Cem%3EHollywood%20Reporter%3C%2Fem%3E%C2%A0executive%20editor%20Stephen%20Galloway.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20director%E2%80%99s%20son%2C%20Cedric%20Friedkin%2C%20confirmed%20to%20the%20Associated%20Press%20that%C2%A0he%20died%20after%20a%20long%20illness.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CHe%20was%20role%20model%20to%20me%20and%20to%20(my%20brother)%20Jack%2C%E2%80%9D%20his%20son%20said.%20%E2%80%9CHe%20was%20a%20massive%20inspiration.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EAn%20early-career%20Oscar-winner%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhen%20he%20was%20just%20in%20his%2030s%2C%20Friedkin%20burst%20onto%20the%20scene%20in%201971%20with%20gritty%20cop%20drama%20%3Cem%3EThe%20French%20Connection%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20for%20which%20he%20won%20an%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dw.com%2Fen%2Fthe-oscars%2Ft-17455571%5C%22%3EOscar%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20best%20director.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20followed%20that%20with%20iconic%20horror%20film%20and%20box%20office%20hit%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Exorcist%3C%2Fem%3E%C2%A0in%201973%2C%20which%20follows%20a%2012-year-old%20girl%20possessed%20by%20the%20devil.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20film%2C%20which%20attracted%20controversy%20for%20its%20shocking%20scenes%2C%C2%A0won%20two%20Oscars%20and%20spawned%20four%20sequels%20based%20on%20the%20same%20novel%2C%20but%2